@host = http://localhost:5150

### 1. Register a new user. 200 OK with an empty body on success.
# Password must be 6+ chars with upper, lower, digit, and non-alphanumeric.
POST {{host}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "Passw0rd!"
}

### 2. Try a weak password. 400 with a ProblemDetails body listing the failed rules.
POST {{host}}/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "weak@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "abc"
}

### 3. Log in for a TOKEN (no useCookies). Returns { tokenType, accessToken, expiresIn, refreshToken }.
# Copy the accessToken into the @token variable below.
POST {{host}}/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dev@codewithmukesh.com",
  "password": "Passw0rd!"
}

### 4. Call the protected endpoint WITHOUT a token. 401 Unauthorized.
GET {{host}}/api/products

### 5. Call the protected endpoint WITH the token. 200 OK.
@token = PASTE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
GET {{host}}/api/products
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Refresh: exchange the refresh token for a fresh access/refresh pair.
@refreshToken = PASTE_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
POST {{host}}/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 7. Read the current user's info (proves the token authenticates).
GET {{host}}/manage/info
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
